name: Junior (Guest)
description:
TO ADOPT:  Complete an application at www.baltimorecats.org/application 


Animal Lovers,

Junior was rescued when we found his very pregnant mom, Annabelle, on Nov 12th wandering the streets. Junior and his siblings were born on Nov 19th, 2017. 

While all of his siblings have found wonderful homes, Junior remains in search of a home with his mom Annabelle (also posted). 


Annabelle was rescued back in November when she was found wandering the streets with a belly Are you in the market for two super sweet and irresistible lovebugs?!

Annabelle is a very unique girl, certainly with her large bunny ears and spots, she appears to have the characteristics/appearance of an Ocicat. All in all, she is an amazing cat with a great personality! She is a total lap-cat. Annabelle and her baby would love to be the only kitties of the house. :)

Annabelle and Junior have been fixed, vaccinated for rabies and distemper, and disease tested. If you are interested, there is an adoption application I would be happy to share with you. 

 

 

****Junior is NOT part of our adoption program and is listed as a courtesy. For any questions or to adopt him, please e-mail Ellen at elnblonder@yahoo.com****


Ready to adopt?  Visit our website for more information and to get started!  www.baltimorecats.org/application

name: Watson
description:
Watson, Sherlock and their two sisters were born inside and have been raised by awesome foster families. They are ready to go home with you today.

 

This kitty is currently in a loving foster home and has been tested negative for FIV/FELV, microchipped, has age appropriate vaccinations, and has been spayed/neutered. 

Please put in an adoption application on our website, cats-can.org if you are interested or if you have any questions please email us at kittyrescuetnr@gmail.com


C.A.T.S.-C.A.N., Inc. is a non-profit organization based in Geneva, Florida. We operate a no-kill shelter and have cats and kittens up for adoption at Oviedo Petsmart. We screen each applicant Please put in an application or come by to see our kitties! We have an adoption event every Saturday from11:00 - 5:00 and some Sunday's Noon to 4:00 (please check our Facebook to make sure we're there!) at the Oviedo Petsmart. You can also visit a few of our resident cats every day in the Petsmart Cat room!

Cats-Can Does Not Permit Declawing - For more information on Declawing, please visit our Feline Care Tips Menu on our homepage and visit our webpages (under special needs) of wonderful cats that are already declawed looking for new homes.

Know someone who needs low-cost, high-quality spay/neuter services for their pets? Have them contact SpayNSave at 407-920-4894 for clinic dates, information and appointments. They work with feral cats, domestic cats and also offer spay and neuter services for dogs. Contact us today!

name: Rajah (Fostered in CT)
description:
Angels Among Us Animal Rescue announces a new Angel:


Meet Rajah!

This precious little guy is 5 months old (DOB 10/1/17), neutered and healthy. He is loving but a little shy and nervous. He is and should continue to be an indoor cat. Rajah is ready to go to his forever home!

Rajah  is  up to date on vaccines and rabies, micro chipped and neutered.  He is located in CT and his adoption donation is $150. 

If you are interested in opening your home to a wonderful kitty please visit our website at www.angelsamongusanimalrescue.org and fill out an application to adopt.


If you are interested in adopting one of our animals, please go to www.angelsamongusanimalrescue.org and fill out an online adoption application. Thank you!
 
Massachusetts Residents: Effective September 28, 2017 a Quarantine Fee of $120 will be required (in addition to the adoption fee) to adopt a dog that has been Quarantined. Massachusetts mandates that all dogs entering MA shall be quarantined for 48 hours in a state approved facility.

name: Crimson Chin
description:
Name:  Crimson Chin
Age:  4 mos.
Reason for surrender:  Stray 
Animal ID#: 36938468 

 

Hi, my name is Crimson Chin.  Strange name you say? I get it because I have the cutest black spot on my chin and I love to have my chin scratched.  Also, I stick it out so far that my foster parents say I look like the cartoon character Crimson Chin.  I'm a low key kitten.  I like to relax most of the time by myself.  I enjoy warm spots like the radiators or the sun light shining in the window.  I like to play once in a while but relaxing and sleeping is my favorite thing to do.  It has taken me a while to warm up to my foster parents, please don't hold that against me, I'm a shy guy.  I like to be in the same room as you but just sit back and watch what is going on.  I love to eat and I have grown to trust my foster parents with treats, I can do the same thing with you!   I currently live with cats and dogs.  Dogs are a no-go, I do not like those silly canines! Cats are fine.  If you are interested in meeting me please contact my foster parents at jrmc610@gmail.com  

 

Looking forward to meeting you!  

Current location: Foster care (this pet is not at the shelter)
www.phillypaws.org
Please apply online by emailing  adoptions@phillypaws.org .

(posted by ST on 3-13-18)


PAWS, the Philadelphia Animal Welfare Society, is a 501(c)3 non-profit animal rescue organization. PAWS pulls at-risk animals from the City of Philadelphia's animal control shelter and adopts them out from several locations: our Old City adoption center (2nd and Arch Streets), our Northeast Adoption Center (1810 Grant Avenue); our Wellness Clinic at 2900 Grays Ferry Avenue; our adoption locations at the South Philly and Cottman Avenue PetSmart stores; and, our network of foster homes.

PAWS is dedicated to saving the lives of Philadelphia's homeless, abandoned and unwanted animals and is working to make Philadelphia a city in which every healthy and treatable pet is guaranteed a home.

When you adopt a pet from PAWS you truly save a life!

Please reference this animal's ID NUMBER when inquiring about this pet. Both PAWS Adoption Centers are open Monday-Friday from 12 p.m. to 7 p.m., Saturday 11 a.m. to 7 p.m., and Sunday from 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. PAWS' Wellness Clinic is open Monday - Sunday from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m., but appointments are required for adoptions.

Adoption fees include age-appropriate vaccinations, spaying/neutering, and microchipping. No animals may be adopted without being spayed or neutered. Adoption fees are as follows, plus tax: $150 for large adult dogs (older than 1 year); $250 for small dogs (under 25 lbs) and all puppies (under 1 year); $60 for adult cats (over 6 months of age), and $100 for kittens (under 6 months of age). When you adopt a pair of kittens together, the total adoption fee is $150.

Please visit our web site, www.phillypaws.org, for our full calendar of adoption events throughout the region, and for more information on adopting, fostering, volunteering, or donating.

PAWS is dedicated to saving the lives of Philadelphia's homeless, abandoned and unwanted animals and is working to make Philadelphia a city in which every healthy and treatable pet is guaranteed a home.

When you adopt a pet from PAWS you truly save a life!

Please reference this animal's ID NUMBER when inquiring about this pet. Both PAWS Adoption Centers are open Monday-Friday from 12 p.m. to 7 p.m., Saturday 11 a.m. to 7 p.m., and Sunday from 11 a.m. to 6 p.m. PAWS' Wellness Clinic is open Monday - Sunday from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m., but appointments are required for adoptions.

Adoption fees include age-appropriate vaccinations, spaying/neutering, and microchipping. No animals may be adopted without being spayed or neutered. Adoption fees are as follows, plus tax: $150 for large adult dogs (older than 1 year); $250 for small dogs (under 25 lbs) and all puppies (under 1 year); $60 for adult cats (over 6 months of age), and $100 for kittens (under 6 months of age). When you adopt a pair of kittens together, the total adoption fee is $150.

Please visit our web site, www.phillypaws.org, for our full calendar of adoption events throughout the region, and for more information on adopting, fostering, volunteering, or donating.

Name: Crimson Chin Age: 4 mos. Reason for surrender: Stray  Animal ID#: 36938468 

  

 Hi, my name is Crimson Chin. Strange name you say? I get it because I have the cutest black spot on my chin and I love to have my chin scratched. Also, I stick it out so far that my foster parents say I look like the cartoon character Crimson Chin. I'm a low key kitten. I like to relax most of the time by myself. I enjoy warm spots like the radiators or the sun light shining in the window. I like to play once in a while but relaxing and sleeping is my favorite thing to do. It has taken me a while to warm up to my foster parents, please don't hold that against me, I'm a shy guy. I like to be in the same room as you but just sit back and watch what is going on. I love to eat and I have grown to trust my foster parents with treats, I can do the same thing with you!  I currently live with cats and dogs. Dogs are a no-go, I do not like those silly canines! Cats are fine. If you are interested in meeting me please contact my foster parents at jrmc610@gmail.com 

  

 Looking forward to meeting you!

name: TIGGER
description: Meow! I''m so glad you''re thinking about adopting a new fur-ever family member. To help you with your big decision, here are a few things you should know. First, cats just want to be happy and feel loved. Living inside and being a part of the family is really important to us. A lot of the things you need as humans to stay happy and healthy, us cats need too. We depend on you for things like vet visits, nutritious food, clean water, toys, play time and of course, lots of love and attention! Did you know that cats live 15 to 20 years on average? That''s a lifetime of love! So thanks for stopping by, I hope you''ll keep me in mind when you make your big decision!

name: Marvelous Mateo
description:
Say hello to the marvelous Mateo, a loving & friendly young tabby ready to move into his forever home! Mateo is a sweet little guy who enjoys it when his human fosters speak in funny voices and his favorite toys are ones that dangle from strings. His days are spent in pursuit of  “play” with the 2 other cats in his foster home, he is always down for a game of chase! He is very responsive, affectionate and enjoys the company of people. Mateo is best to go to a home with other cats and with some one searching for a fully present animal companion who will liven things up and return your affection one hundred times over!

Mateo is fully vaccinated, tested negative for FeLV/FIV, spayed and parasite free. If you’d like to arrange a play date with Mateo or for further information please contact Belinda -        Belinda @BrooklynAnimalAction.org

Thank you for considering one of our rescued kitties, your support allows us to make room for the next furry friend in need. BrooklynAnimalAction.org

name: Zelda
description: It is so easy to fall in love with Zelda. She is the kind of kitten that you can wrap up in a blanket and snuggle in your arms. Anyone coming within five feet will activate her purr motor. She loves to stay by your side or sit on your lap while you gently stroke her and give her kisses on her nose. Her previous adopter returned her citing intestinal problems. However, they may not have followed their vet's recommendations on treatment. Zelda was seen by our vet who put her on a special high fiber diet and she has been responding very well. She appears to be back to normal but we are taking it slow so we can be certain. It is possible that she may need to be on a high fiber diet indefinitely. Zelda is a spayed female kitten. Her estimated birthday is 7/26/2017. She is microchipped and current on her vaccines. Zelda is in a foster home and is available by appointment. Interested adopters should fill out an application. If you are renting your home please bring a copy of your lease allowing pets.

name: Gertrude (Gerty)
description:
We are trying to help find a new home for Gerty. She is a courtesy listing and not a cat for adoption at For the Love of Cats. For the Love of Cats cannot provide or guarantee any health information or background on this cat.

Gerty is a very affectionate 3 year old black female cat. She purrs a lot once she becomes accustomed to her environment. Chatters a lot. Likes to sleep at foot of my bed. Enjoys being a lap kitty (on her terms). Still "young" and she will have moments of playfulness. Enjoys using our tall cat perch to relax. Doesn't mind other cats, but is more of a loner. I have to give her up because of health issues and allergies.

 Please contact Carrie at 239-682-2664 or email clfales92@aol.com.

Gerty is spayed, up to date on vaccinations and microchipped.
